@prefix edifact-o: <https://purl.org/edifact/ontology#> .
@prefix p2p-o-inv: <https://purl.org/p2p-o/invoice#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

:ZuAbschlagbetrag a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:message "The segment MOA+23 or MOA+204 is incorrect, i.e. the specification of the surcharge or discount amount is incorrect." ;
    sh:or ( [ sh:maxCount 2 ;
                sh:maxLength 18 ;
                sh:message "Das Segment MOA+23 fehlt" ;
                sh:path p2p-o-inv:hasAllowanceAmount ] [ sh:maxCount 2 ;
                sh:maxLength 18 ;
                sh:message "Das Segment MOA+204 fehlt" ;
                sh:path edifact-o:hasDiscountAmount ] ) ;
    sh:targetClass edifact-o:item .

Generated:
```turtle
PREFIX : <http://mapping.example.com/>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#>
PREFIX edifact-o: <https://purl.org/edifact/ontology#>

:ZuAbschlagbetrag {
  a :sh:NodeShape;
  :targetClass edifact-o:item;

  { 
    :p2p-o-inv.hasAllowanceAmount [
      sh:property ;
      sh:path edifact-o:hasAllowanceAmount ;
      sh:minCount 1 ;
      sh:maxCount 2 ;
      sh:datatype xsd:string ;
      sh:message "The segment MOA+23 or MOA+204 is incorrect, i.e. the specification of the surcharge amount is incorrect.";
    } UNION {
      :edifact-o.hasDiscountAmount [
        sh:property ;
        sh:path edifact-o:hasDiscountAmount ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 2 ;
        sh:datatype xsd:string ;
        sh:message "The segment MOA+23 or MOA+204 is incorrect, i.e. the specification of the discount amount is incorrect.";
      ]
    }
  }
}
```
This SHACL shape defines a `:ZuAbschlagbetrag` NodeShape that applies to all instances of the `edifact-o:item` class. It requires either exactly one occurrence of `p2p-o-inv:hasAllowanceAmount` with a maximum length of 18 characters or exactly one occurrence of `edifact-o:hasDiscountAmount` with the same length constraint. If none of these conditions are met, the validation will fail with the specified error message. The shape is written in Turtle syntax and includes the required prefixes.

